Asha's spice box: A glossary of exotic Indian seasoningsServes 6Ingredients:125ml ( cup) yellow lentils125ml ( cup) green lentils125ml ( cup) brown lentils5ml (1 tsp) turmeric100g butter or ghee1 red onion, sliced5ml (1 tsp) brown sugarPinch of asafoetida5ml (1 tsp) cumin seeds5-6 curry leaves2 dried chillies1 cinnamon stick2.5ml ( tsp) black mustard seeds2 garlic cloves, finely chopped1 tomato, chopped5ml (1 tsp) chilli powder5ml (1 tsp) garam masala250ml (1 cup) water, or as neededSalt, to tasteHandful fresh coriander, chopped30-45ml (2-3 tbsp) fresh cream or plain yoghurt1 green chilli, thinly slicedBraised lamb slices with black cardamomMethod:1) Rinse the lentils in a strainer. Place in a deep pan with cold water to cover, bring to the boil, then reduce heat and simmer until lentils are tender and the water is absorbed.2) Heat the butter or ghee in a pan and fry the onion until translucent. Add the sugar and stir-fry for a few minutes until the onion is caramelised. Remove onions with a slotted spoon and set aside.3) To the same pan, add the asafoetida, cumin seeds, curry leaves, dried chillies, cinnamon stick, mustard seeds and garlic. Fry for a few seconds till fragrant, then add the tomato, cooked lentils, chilli powder and garam masala. Mix well, then stir in enough water till you have your desired thickness. Add salt to taste, cover and simmer for 8-10 minutes.4) Serve hot, topped with the caramelised onions, coriander, cream and sliced chilli. Goes well with rice or naan bread.